news.title: To protect buyers, Jaipur development body will list illegal flats on website
news.para: The civic body will mention the list of approved projects in every zone. Moreover, it will display a list of illegal and sealed apartments on its website.

news.title: Submit proposal to reduce building misuse penalties: MHA tells Chandigarh admin
news.para: The response comes after UT's request of giving powers to the UT administrator. Last year, the ministry had asked the UT to submit afresh proposal and the UT had sought some clarifications.

news.title: Kanpur: Cheaters dupe in name of house allotment, six arrested
news.para: Crime branch officials said that their network spread in many other cities of the country. The Crime branch has arrested six accused and freezed 6.5 lakh rupees of fraud in their accounts.

news.title: Your-Space raises $10 million in series 'A' funding
news.para: The investment round also saw participation from Manish Choksi’s (Vice Chairman at Asian Paints) family office, Sunidhi Group’s family office, Sanjaya Gupta (former MD & CEO of PNBHFL), amongst others.

news.title: Thane: EOW arrests builder for duping 43 investors of Rs 5.5 crore
news.para: The accused, Manmohan Ailinsanghani, was nabbed at the airport on his return from Dubai, said Sunil Lokhande, DCP EOW, Thane police.

news.title: Sebi tightens rules governing utilisation of IPO proceeds
news.para: ​ Also, the regulator has extended anchor investors' lock-in period to 90 days and now, funds reserved for general corporate purposes will be monitored by credit rating agencies, according to a notification issued on January 14.

news.title: Supreme court wants model builder-buyer agreement in place
news.para: The supreme court said that it wants that instead of leaving it to the States, the Centre makes the model builder-buyer agreement and model agent-buyer agreement which shall be applicable for the whole of the country.

news.title: Prestige Estates records sales bookings of Rs 4,268 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: The Bengaluru-based Prestige group has also clocked the highest-ever collections of Rs 2,431.6 crore during the December quarter, up 70 per cent year-on-year.

news.title: SC directs Supertech to enter into contract within week with firm to demolish twin-towers
news.para: The NOIDA authority informed the bench that it has finalised the company Edifice Engineering for demolishing the twin towers in consultation with the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) Roorkee.

news.title: China: Country Garden sees bonds slump
news.para: Last week was the worst on record for Country Garden's bonds and fresh falls of up to 17 points on Monday left most of its international market debt at 25-35 percent below its face value.

news.title: UltraTech announces Rs 965-crore capex for modernisation, doubling Birla White production capacity
news.para: The Aditya Birla Group company plans to increase the capacity of Birla White from the current 6.5 lakh tonnes per annum (LTPA) to 12.53 LTPA, UltraTech Cement said in a post-earnings statement.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's profit up 7.9% at Rs 1,710.14 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations rose by 5.89 per cent to Rs 12,984.93 crore during the quarter under review compared to Rs 12,262 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal, the company said in a BSE filing.

news.title: Mindspace REIT to raise up to Rs 500 crore through issue of NCDs
news.para: The executive committee of K Raheja Corp Investment Managers LLP, the manager to the REIT has approved the issue of listed, rated, secured, non-cumulative, taxable, transferable, redeemable NCDs by the REIT.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to invest Rs 900 crore to develop residential project in Mumbai
news.para: Ajmera Realty and Infra India estimates sales of Rs 1,500 crore from the project, which will comprise 540 residential flats and 18 retail shops.

news.title: Inaya Living buys South Mumbai bungalow Laburnum House for Rs 93 crore
news.para: The development company has bought the property through its parent Chandler & Price (India) that has paid stamp duty worth Rs 4.65 crore for the registration of the transaction.
